what have i done to deserve this i have suffered from debilitating mental illnesses for half of my life and am now years old i can never find anyone who is willing to befriend me and i have suffered constant rejection from peers for many years now meds stopped working a couple of years ago and i slipped into a very deep depression however i have finally found medication that is working sort of and am beginning to feel better when all of a sudden something else comes up i am now dealing with heart problems that may be life threatening and guess what these meds that are helping me mentally are aggrevating my heart condition which means that i'll probably have to stop taking them it's one crisis after the next with no end in sight it's like this imagine being in a terrible storm for many years when finally it begins to fade the sun comes out the birds begin to sing and happiness returns then all of a sudden a bigger storm comes along and this one is twice as bad as the first i can't take it to quote the immortal words of clint eastwood in unforgiven deserve ain't got nuthin' to do with it there is no reason for it there is no cosmic plan there is no sin you or your parents committed millions suffer and die as a result of mental illness terminal illness and genetic disorders none of them deserve it either i'm sorry you have to go through this but i am certain you are not alone all i can tell you is to reject self pity accept what you can't change and work on what you can i wish you the best of luck Clint Eastwood Medicine Suicide Charles Darwin's illness Mental illness Original sin Autism Anorexia nervosa Narcissism Chronic fatigue syndrome Transsexuality Theory of conduct Multiple sclerosis Panic attack Sin City Sigmund Freud Jon Secada Borderline personality disorder Alcoholism Bipolar disorder Shaggy dog story Psychiatric hospital Religion Clinical depression Hikikomori Abortion Post-traumatic stress disorder The Brothers Karamazov Gender identity disorder Stroke Tra